  "prompt": "What are examples of prefixes and suffixes?",
  "response": "Prefixes are added to the beginning of a root word while suffixes are added to the end of a root word. Here are some common examples:\n\nPrefixes:\n1. Un- (e.g. unhappy, unlock, unusual): meaning not or the opposite of\n2. Re- (e.g. redo, reuse, replay): meaning again or back\n3. Dis- (e.g. disagree, disappear, dislike): meaning not or opposite of\n4. In- (e.g. inactive, incorrect, inadequate): meaning not or opposite of\n5. Pre- (e.g. preheat, preview, preschool): meaning before\n\nSuffixes:\n1. -ly (e.g. quickly, slowly, happily): meaning in a certain way\n2. -ful (e.g. joyful, careful, helpful): meaning full of\n3. -ness (e.g. happiness, kindness, darkness): meaning state or quality\n4. -less (e.g. hopeless, endless, fearless): meaning without\n5. -able (e.g. comfortable, washable, readable): meaning capable of or worthy of.",
